cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.ST

The paper discusses a new method for simulation-based inference using neural network-based conditional density estimators. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method is also applicable to systems and control (cs.SY) as it deals with stochastic simulators. The paper mentions the ability to operate on high-dimensional image data, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another possible category. Finally, the method is scalable and efficient, which could also place it under statistics (cs.ST).
